1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will delve deeper into the media library.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
We will learn to navigate and manage the media library, add ALT text and also understand the importance of optimizing images.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Media consists of the images, video recordings and files that you upload and use in your site.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
And of course, media is inserted into pages and posts.

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
I also think you'll agree, media plays a crucial role in enhancing the overall experience and effectiveness of a website.

6
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
You can add various types of media to your library, from photos, screenshots, audio, PDF documents, spreadsheets, PowerPoint presentations and more.

7
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
When you open your media library, it will open to the default grid view.

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
And in the grid view, thumbnails of images, audio icons etc are all arranged in grid structure.

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
And here you are able to filter through your media to find what you are looking for.

10
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
At the top, next to the grid view icon, you can filter your media by media type and date.

11
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
The All media items drop down allows you to select by the types of media, such as images, audio, video, documents and even spreadsheets.

12
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
You can also view any media that is unattached to any posts or pages.

13
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
And this means the media is in your media library, but you haven't used it anywhere on your site.

14
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Let's use the filtering option, for example, to only see audio files.

15
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Or documents, like a PDF.

16
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Or even spreadsheets.

17
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:50,000
And then of course, you can just go back to seeing all media items.

18
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Next, the All dates drop down allows you to view images based on their upload dates.

19
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
You can quickly find media you have uploaded in a specific month, or you may choose to view all.

20
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
When you click on Bulk select, you can delete media simultaneously.

21
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
You can also search for media using the search block top right, by for example using words from the description or file name.

22
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
In this case, I would like to see all my shoe related images, all done with a simple search.

23
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
You can also view your media in List View.

24
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
In List View, all your media will be listed below each other, as the name implies.

25
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
And you will also be able to see the file name and what type of file it is, for example a PDF or JPEG.

26
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
To add media to your library, click on Add new media file in the sidebar or at the top.

27
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Once selected, you will be able to drag and drop single or multiple files into the page, or use the select files option.

28
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
When you add media to a page or a post using the Image block or the Gallery block for example,

29
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
you will be able to upload images directly from your computer into your post or page and media library, or directly from your media library.

30
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,000
When it comes to larger videos, it's better to embed them via the YouTube block or the Video block, as it will save space in your media library and for better performance.

31
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
When you open an image, you will be able to add attributes such as alternative text, the title, a caption and a description.

32
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
It is important to always add ALT text to an image.

33
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
The ALT text is a concise description of an image for users who can't view the image, and it's also good for your site's SEO or your site's search engine optimization.

34
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Adding a description also enhances SEO and allows for better organization and understanding of the image's purpose or content.

35
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
When you click on Edit image, you will be able to crop the image as well as scaling it or resizing it for image optimization.

36
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,000
The dimensions update automatically once you change the height or the width.

37
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
And don't be concerned, when you select Restore original image, you can restore the image to its original format.

38
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
You also have the option to rotate or to flip the image.

39
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
To end off, let's briefly talk about image optimization.

40
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:53,000
It is advised to optimize images before uploading them to your media library, to improve page load speed and save service space.

41
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
You can use web-based tools to achieve this, for example sites like TinyPNG, Bulk Resize or Squoosh.app to only name a few.

42
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Remember to save images with a descriptive and relevant file name before adding it to your media library.

43
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:24,000
It helps search engines understand the content of the image, contributing to better SEO.

44
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Search engines may use file names as a factor when indexing and ranking content.

45
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Another option is to use an image optimization plugin.

46
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,000
There are various image optimization plugins available to choose from when you search the plugins directory.

47
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
When you find the plugin that suits your needs, you can install and activate and follow the necessary steps.

48
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Both of these methods, using a web-based tool or plugin, improve overall performance by compressing images without compromising visual quality.

49
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
All the best as you use the media library to elevate your site to the next level.

